Supplementary Material 2:Complete Pseudo-code for H2OML
    # ================= Configuration Parameters =================
    train_ratio ← 0.7                # Proportion of training set
    random_seed ← 42              # Random seed for reproducibility
    max_runtime_secs ← 600         # Maximum runtime for H2O AutoML (seconds)
    sort_metric ← MAE             # Metric used to rank models
    top_features_per_model ← 10     # Number of top features per model
    top_aggregate_features ← 15     # Number of top features for aggregate importance
    target_column ← "Gas close"      # Prediction target
    time_column ← "Date"           # Time column

    # ================= Step 1: Load and Process Data =================
    data ← Read Excel(FilePath)
    Convert data[time_column] to datetime
    Sort data by time_column ascending
    feature_columns ← All columns in data excluding target_column and time_column

    # ================= Step 2: Time-based Train/Test Split =================
    total_samples ← Number of rows in data
    train_samples ← floor(total_samples * train_ratio)
    train_data ← data[1 to train_samples]
    test_data ← data[train_samples+1 to total_samples]

    # Convert to H2OFrame
    H2O_train ← Convert to H2OFrame(train_data)
    H2O_test ← Convert to H2OFrame(test_data)

    # ================= Step 3: Initialize H2O AutoML =================
    Initialize H2O AutoML with:
        - max_runtime_secs = max_runtime_secs
        - seed = random_seed
        - sort_metric = sort_metric
    Train AutoML on H2O_train:
        - Inputs = feature_columns
        - Output = target_column

    # ================= Step 4: Get Leaderboard =================
    leaderboard ← AutoML leaderboard
    model_ids ← List of all model IDs in leaderboard

    # ===========Step 5: Model Evaluation and Feature Importance ==========
    For each model_id in model_ids:
        model ← Load model(model_id)
        
        # Evaluate on test set
        performance ← Compute MAE, RMSE, MSE, R2 on H2O_test
        Record performance with model_id

        # Feature importance
        var_importance ← Get feature importance of model
        If var_importance exists:
            top_features ← Select top top_features_per_model features by importance
            Record var_importance and top_features
        Else:
            Record var_importance as None
        End If
    End For

    # ==========Step 6: Compute Aggregate Feature Importance ===============
    all_var_importance ← Collect feature importance from all models
    For each feature:
        avg_importance ← Average importance across models
        avg_rank ← Average rank across models
        num_models ← Number of models including the feature
    Sort features by avg_importance descending

    # ================= Step 7: Plot Feature Importance =================
    For the top 3 model_ids:
        Plot feature importance for model (top top_features_per_model)
    End For
    Plot aggregate feature importance (top top_aggregate_features)

    # ================= Step 8: Save Results =================
    Save all model performances to CSV
    Save aggregate feature importance summary to CSV
    Save each model's feature importance to CSV
    Save aggregate feature importance plot (PNG and PDF)
    Save each model's feature importance plot (PNG and PDF)

    # ================= Step 9: Shutdown H2O =================
    Shutdown H2O cluster
End Procedure
